The paper deals with the problem of accurately localizing the pupil centre for gaze tracking in real-world conditions. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a dataset (LPW) for evaluation, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also involves filtering and tracking techniques, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
